Nollywood actress Tayo Sobola aka Sotayo has promised to put smiles on people’s faces after setting up a foundation, Sobola Tayo Anthonia (STA) foundation. The fashionable celebrity, through the foundation, reached out to the less privileged recently. The new foundation gave out relief packs that contains food items and provisions to indigents around Lagos, Nigeria.   Anticipate my s3x- scandal – Harrysong     My daughters ask why their mums are different – Davido     Olamide teases new song with Wizkid   Speaking on this new project, Sotayo said, “I just want to use this platform to give back to the people. Government alone can’t do it all, we as people too should strive to cater for one another, especially those that are less privileged among us. My vision is to continue to bring smiles to the faces of people in my own little ways.” Continuing, she said, “We shall continue to positively impact the lives of the people and also in the empowerment of the girl-child,” she further stated. The mantra of the foundation is “touching lives.” Sotayo has featured in many Yoruba and English movie productions, and her self-produced movies include Corper Jide, Bella, Arewa Onijogbon, among many others.